

1) Get Command Line Args (FibInputs Class)
   Use get_opt_long to parse command line
   Need to get/set
      verbose flag (bool)
      num_iterations (unsigned long)
      color (unsigned int)
      output file name (string)

2) Generate Fibonacci Word (FibWord Class)
      For num_iterations, append bits to string based on
      Fib fractal rules

3) Build Directions List (Directions Class)
      For number of bits in string, build list of directions.

4) Build Fibonacci Fractal (FibFractal Class)
      For each listed direction, set pixel data for segements

5) Output Fibonacci Fractal (FibFractal Class)
      Output pixel data to output file name

Base Classes-->ExtendedClasses:
MyInputParser--> FibInputParser
MyInput-->FibInput
MyFractal-->FibFractal
MyUtils

class FibFracInputs
   parseArgs( argv, argc )
   bool verbose
   unsigned long num_iterations
   unsigned int color
   string output_file

class FibWord
   genFibWord( num_iterations )
   string fib_word

class Directions
   genDirections( fib_word )
   list<Direction> dir_list

class FibFractal
   setFibFractal( dir_list )
   outputtoFile( file_name )
   

